      "writtenOn": "2018-08-28T19:08:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Do I have to care about N32 being RGBA vs BGRA for Android??\n\nYes, but really, we support both configs, regardless of the platform.\n\n\u003e \n\u003e Again, using a swizzler will fix this, but I\u0027m having troubles getting that to work.\n\nWhat problems are you having? I\u0027m happy to help!\n\nThe swizzler is also helpful for handling sampled decodes.\n\nI see in your other comment that you plan to leave that for a follow-on CL. Since this is not enabled by default, I think it\u0027s fine to just wait until you have the swizzler and let that take care of it.",
      "parentUuid": "11b0d0fe_c78aac60",
